-- Montenegrin President Set to Ask Djukanovic to Return as Premier
-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 2012-11-09T17:02:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-09/montenegrin-president-set-to-ask-djukanovic-to-return-as-premier.html
Montenegro’s President Filip
Vujanovic will ask ally Milo Djukanovic to return to head the
government of the smallest former Yugoslav republic as it looks
to join the European Union, according to a statement on the
president’s  website .  Djukanovic, 50, who has previously served as premier and
president of the Adriatic nation, will replace Igor Luksic to
form a Cabinet after his  Democratic Party  of Socialists won last
month’s parliamentary elections.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Misha Savic in Belgrade at 
 msavic2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  